The problem statement is provided in top-level file : PROBLEM_STATEMENT

The project uses DFS-sinking to evaluate the area size of the asymmetrical shaped fertile lands and returns the sorted sizes.

The memory constraints of the project to run on 400x600 area is 32MB so pass the argument:
-Xss32m

The pom uses JUnit5 and is self sufficient in terms of dependencies and versions of compiler or dependencies used.

A number of tests have been used in development of this assignment and are provided as JUnit tests in FarmTest.java under src/test/java sub-directory.

Feel free to rach out at chandniverma2112@gmail.com for any clarifications on the code.